To run sentiment_parse:

1) Install nltk:
    sudo pip install -U nltk

2) Specify the path of the "basic_sentiment_analysis.py" file to PYTHONPATH, for example:
   export PYTHONPATH="$HOME/hansonrobotics/opencog/opencog/opencog/"

3) Specify the path of the dictionary files, for example:
   export OPENCOG_PATH="$HOME/hansonrobotics/opencog/opencog/opencog/"

   or change the path in the basic_sentiment_analysis.py code (line 156-157):

   path = os.environ['OPENCOG_PATH'] + 'nlp/chatbot/'
   dicttagger = DictionaryTagger([path + 'dicts/positive.yml',
         path + 'dicts/negative.yml', path + 'dicts/inc.yml', path + 'dicts/dec.yml', path + 'dicts/inv.yml'])

3) run nlp-parse, follow the InheritanceLink to check the sentiment of the sentence:
guile> (cog-incoming-set (car (nlp-parse "This is not a disgusting test.")))
((InheritanceLink
   (SentenceNode "sentence@d6584821-3683-47a5-b77f-8971e20db8cb")
   (ConceptNode "Positive")
)
 (ParseLink (stv 1 1)
   (ParseNode "sentence@d6584821-3683-47a5-b77f-8971e20db8cb_parse_0" (stv 1 0.61070001))
   (SentenceNode "sentence@d6584821-3683-47a5-b77f-8971e20db8cb")
)
 (SentenceSequenceLink (stv 1 1)
   (SentenceNode "sentence@d6584821-3683-47a5-b77f-8971e20db8cb")
   (NumberNode "612.000000")
)
 (ListLink
   (Node "This is not a disgusting test.")
   (SentenceNode "sentence@d6584821-3683-47a5-b77f-8971e20db8cb")
)
)
